webpackJsonp([0xaf33152b43f8],{723:function(a,e){a.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<blockquote><p>\n  &#8220;With a kick, snare, kicks and high hat, skilled in the trade of that old boom bap&#8221;\n</p></blockquote>\n<p>Before I was a software engineer, I was a music producer. Specifically, I made beats for rap songs. Then file sharing put a dent in the music industry, and it became much harder to do as a career. But hey, I had programming to fall back on!</p>\n<p>I still made music as a hobby over the years, but less and less seriously as time went on. Very recently, I got news that Akai was discontinuing its iconic offering of standalone hardware MPC drum machines. This made me deeply sad. I mowed untold numbers of lawns for my first MPC and it felt to me like the death of an era.</p>\n<figure id="media-758" class="align-center">\n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; z-index: 0 !important;; max-width: 771px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 74.96757457846954%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;" alt="akai mpc2000 top lg 771x578" title="" src="/static/akai-mpc2000_top_lg-771x578-21c2eb22579766bd7ad80e23513e43a3-c40b2.jpg" srcset="/static/akai-mpc2000_top_lg-771x578-21c2eb22579766bd7ad80e23513e43a3-de3ab.jpg 200w,\n/static/akai-mpc2000_top_lg-771x578-21c2eb22579766bd7ad80e23513e43a3-35eff.jpg 400w,\n/static/akai-mpc2000_top_lg-771x578-21c2eb22579766bd7ad80e23513e43a3-c40b2.jpg 771w" sizes="(max-width: 771px) 100vw, 771px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </figure>\n<p>So I did what any geek that writes React code all day long would do. I wrote a library so that I can make beats with ReactJS. I call it <code>react-music</code>.</p>\n<p><code>react-music</code> let you make beats using JSX code and hooks into the Web Audio API to turn your code into beautiful music. There is no UI, with the exception of a play/stop button and a spectrum analyzer that renders on your page:</p>\n<figure id="media-763" class="align-center">\n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; z-index: 0 !important;; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 75.90361445783132%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;" alt="=" title="" src="/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-11.45.11-AM-1a4b9dd3f864a8176bc1072ace58fad4-fc76f.png" srcset="/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-11.45.11-AM-1a4b9dd3f864a8176bc1072ace58fad4-290b0.png 200w,\n/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-11.45.11-AM-1a4b9dd3f864a8176bc1072ace58fad4-14201.png 400w,\n/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-11.45.11-AM-1a4b9dd3f864a8176bc1072ace58fad4-fc76f.png 800w,\n/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-11.45.11-AM-1a4b9dd3f864a8176bc1072ace58fad4-0b4a0.png 996w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </figure>\n<p>The code is regular React components that implements the sort of features you might find in a sequencer/sampler/DAW via the props API:</p>\n<figure id="media-770" class="align-center">\n  <span class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper" style="position: relative; display: block; z-index: 0 !important;; max-width: 796px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">\n    <span class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image" style="padding-bottom: 43.96984924623115%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;">\n      <img class="gatsby-resp-image-image" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;" alt="Screen Shot 2016 08 22 at 1 15 15 PM" title="" src="/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-1.15.15-PM-9a3856974f1350308356bbda5c1e07c8-29615.png" srcset="/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-1.15.15-PM-9a3856974f1350308356bbda5c1e07c8-6423b.png 200w,\n/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-1.15.15-PM-9a3856974f1350308356bbda5c1e07c8-e5417.png 400w,\n/static/Screen-Shot-2016-08-22-at-1.15.15-PM-9a3856974f1350308356bbda5c1e07c8-29615.png 796w" sizes="(max-width: 796px) 100vw, 796px">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </figure>\n<p>Open up your running app in a browser, and now you have super hot beats:</p>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/hslFWOfao7o?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<p>The library is still very young at this point, and has a lot of work on the roadmap, but if you&#8217;d like to make some hot fire with the power of React, check it out here:</p>\n<p><a href="https://github.com/FormidableLabs/react-music">https://github.com/FormidableLabs/react-music</a></p>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 9.090909090909092%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=formidablelabs&amp;repo=react-music&amp;type=star&amp;count=true&amp;size=large" frameborder="0" scrolling="0" style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 9.090909090909092%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;"\n          >\n            <iframe src="https://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=kenwheeler&amp;type=follow&amp;count=true&amp;size=large" frameborder="0" scrolling="0" style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>',fields:{slug:"/blog/2016/08/22/make-dope-beats-with-reactjs/"},frontmatter:{id:21,authorId:9,categoryIds:[5,6,1],date:"2016-08-22",pageDescription:"Using react-music to make music in react",pageKeywords:"react, music, mpc, reactjs",pageTitle:"",path:"/2016/08/22/make-dope-beats-with-reactjs/",title:"Make Dope Beats with ReactJS"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/blog/2016/08/22/make-dope-beats-with-reactjs/",prev:{fields:{slug:"/blog/2016/08/15/introducing-webpack-dashboard/"},frontmatter:{authorId:9,categoryIds:[5,6],date:"2016-08-15",id:20,title:"Introducing Webpack Dashboard"}}}}}});